Whereas, on February 26–27, 2014, armed men in unmarked military uniforms seized key strategic
			 objects in the Autonomous Republic of Crimea (“Crimea”) in  Ukraine,
			 including the building of the Crimean Parliament and airports;

Whereas, as of March 4, 2014, the Government of Ukraine confirms that there are approximately
			 16,000
			 Russian troops occupying Crimea;

Whereas President Obama pledged that the United States will stand with the international community
			 in affirming that there will be costs for any military intervention in
			 Ukraine;

paragraph.text:
strongly condemns the Russian Federation's military incursion into Crimea, in clear violation
			 of Ukraine’s
			 territorial integrity and in contravention of international law;

calls on the Government of the	Russian Federation to immediately withdraw all unauthorized
			 military personnel from
			 Crimea;

calls upon the President to seek to reschedule a meeting of the G8 nations, to take place as
			 soon as practicable, where the participating nations should consider a
			 United States proposal to formally expel the Russian Federation;
